com.fortify.bugtracker.common

Class AbstractBugTrackerProcessRunner

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fortify.processrunner.AbstractProcessRunner
      • com.fortify.bugtracker.common.AbstractBugTrackerProcessRunner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICLIOptionDefinitionProvider
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FoDBugTrackerProcessRunner, SSCBugTrackerProcessRunner

    public abstract class AbstractBugTrackerProcessRunner
extends AbstractProcessRunner

    This AbstractProcessRunner implementation can be configured to submit vulnerabilities to a bug tracker, update issue state, or both. Depending on available processors in the Spring configuration, this implementation will determine the available actions and default action:

    • Only ISourceProcessorSubmitVulnsToTarget available: submitVulnerabilities action enabled and default, others disabled
    • Only ISourceProcessorUpdateVulnsOnTarget available: updateIssueState action enabled and default, others disabled
    • Both ISourceProcessorSubmitVulnsToTarget and ISourceProcessorUpdateVulnsOnTarget available: submitVulnerabilities, updateIssueState and submitVulnerabilitiesAndUpdateIssueState actions enabled, submitVulnerabilitiesAndUpdateIssueState is default action

    Source system implementations must extend this class, providing the source system name in the constructor, and annotated with the Component annotation.

    Author:
    Ruud Senden
